Create a function to sanitize the SSN by removing any non-digit characters and formatting it to the standard XXX-XX-XXXX format.

```javascript
// Function to sanitize the SSN
function sanitizeSSN(ssn) {
    // Remove any non-digit characters
    const sanitizedSSN = ssn.replace(/[^0-9]/g, '');

    // Format the sanitized SSN to the standard XXX-XX-XXXX format
    if (sanitizedSSN.length === 9) {
        return `${sanitizedSSN.substring(0, 3)}-${sanitizedSSN.substring(3, 5)}-${sanitizedSSN.substring(5, 9)}`;
    } else {
        return sanitizedSSN;
    }
}
```

